$ System.Net.FtpWebRequest

`System.Net.FtpWebRequest` derives from → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Net/WebRequest[`WebRequest`] (as also does
→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Net/HttpWebRequest[`System.Net.HttpWebRequest`]).

{ Shortcomings

 `S.N.FtpWebRequest` has some shortcomings, for example, it cannot create or delete folders on the FTP server.
  -
  Therefore, Microsoft → https://github.com/dotnet/platform-compat/blob/master/docs/DE0003.md[does not recommend to use `FtpWebRequest`] for new development and
  refers to a → https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1371964/free-ftp-library[this StackOverflow thread] for alternatives.
  -
  The answer with the most upvotes considers → https://github.com/robinrodricks/FluentFTP[FluentFTP] (MIT licence) as an alternative.

}
